Subject: re: Different Technologies


> Some ways I try to make ships of different races (or even regions)
> vary from each other: customs and regulations. Here are some examples
> of ways I\'ve used to make ships different, from different regions,
> species or organizations:

Throwing some of my own ideas into the mix:

A serious human tragedy due to poor safety features causes the local
interstellar polity to crack down on safety requirements for passenger
carrying ships. This could be a real problem for ship owning characters who
might have to foot the bill to add things like lifeboats, or to take out
things, like flammable panels in the passenger and crew compartments, or
install an extensive, and expensive, safety system of another sort.

A secondary form of interstellar travel can be added which is cheaper or
more fuel efficient than standard Jump Drives, but which is slower than even
Jump-1. Such a drive would not seriously impact the game world, but could be
used for local flavor as certain races might use such a design for bulk, low
priority shipping.

Jump Drives, in and of themselves, can be modified slightly. Add a few hours
to transit time to simulate cheap drives, knock a few off to simulate more
expensive, optimized drives. Similarly, fuel consumption can be varied, or
alternate methods of power generation for Jump Drives can be employed, like
the Annic Nova. A more detailed system for misjump calculation can be
employed, and the drives of different races, or companies, or polities might
have slightly different chances to misjump.

There might be some degree of difficulty in applying parts for a more
expensive or exotic version of Jump Drive. Canonically, it is said that the
Droyne make excellent hand crafter Jump Drives, while the first try of the
Hivers was inferior to "standard" drives. The same core technology may be
there with regard to jump drives, but the actual application could well be
different.

Apply drawbacks to technologies like reactionless thrusters and
contra-gravity. This might explain why certain races or cultures might
prefer another form of technology. There were some good ideas along these
lines in the original Fire, Fusion & Steel. One of the ones that I liked
quite a bit was "mass displacement" as a drawback / advantage for
contra-gravity.
