    'topic' => ' Hello and TNE question',
    'body' => 'At 11:05 AM 12/2/1999 -0600, you wrote:
>I give, what was the big deal about TNE that nobody liked it?  Certainly
>Brilliant Lances and Battle Rider are derived works and cool to read if not
>necessarily play.

Hopefully without igniting any embers..

1) Virus.  This was just too much.  It took many players\' tolerance of
handwaving and shattered it.  It just did too many things, too well, to be
believed.

2) The Setting.  Many people loathed the Reformation Coalition setting,
especially the whole "Star Vikings" bit.  As written, Traveller had become
a sort of high-tech dungeon crawl for lostech goodies to sell at auction
crossed with CIA-esque overthrows of unpopular governments.  The time scale
was just to short.. 80 years?  For that level of destruction and fall back?
 Give me 150 to kill of a few generations of technicians, and maybe.

3) The Rules.  The GDW House Rules need to be buried deep, deep in the same
crypt as Dangerous Journeys.  I feel no shame in calling THR the worst
rules ever produced by GDW.  Combat (my area of interest) was an ungodly
mess.. try killing a PC with a hand gun.

There were some things I liked.. Fire, Fusion & Steel was a leap forward in
concept from the usual big book o\'equipment, and I really like BL/BR, but
the total package just failed.
- -- 

