    'topic' => ' Different Technologies',
    'body' => 'In mail you write:

> IMTU the following space propulsion methods are used:
>
> 1) CG:   good out to 10 planetary diameters, extensive use on small
> craft.
>
> 2) Thrusters:  good out to 1000 solar diameters, used by everyone who
> gets outside the 10 planetary limit.
>
> 3) HEPLAR/Fussion Rockets:  secondary drive for anyone who gets outside
> 1000 solar diameter limit (military and scouts mainly)
>
> 4) Solar Sails:  Idle rich (solar sail races)

Actually, solar sails are also useful for "bulk cargo" transports. The
sort of stuff where you don\'t *care* how long it\'s been in transit as
long as loads show up regularly. Solar sails are sufficient to move
such between planets under control of an autopilot.

And unlike most other means of moving such cargos without human crews,
the low acceleration of solar sails is an *advantage*. It means that
it\'s not worth the effort to even *try* to hijack a cargo to use as
"deadfall ordinance" on a planet. It\'ll take so long to get there that
they *can\'t* miss the fact that there\'s something wrong, and they\'ll
have *plenty* of time to intercept the load. 

