    'topic' => ' LEO\'s',
    'body' => 'Actually, Cracker was set in Liverpool.

(New) Scotland Yard is indeed the HQ of the Metropolitan Police (London),
but as a result has a lot of expertise in various areas of policing due to
the size of London, and through it\'s lengthy history.

It will often advise other regional Police Forces, if requested, as it has
many top experts in the more esoteric fields of criminology. It also has a
legacy in fiction dating back to Sherlock Holmes, as being the home of all
the \'top\' detectives.

This is probably due to authors in the 19thC and early 20thC having a London
bias, and also the fact that at this time Scotland Yard was one of the
foremost places world-wide in many early aspects of forensic detection, eg
Fingerprints etc.

Many well publicised crimes of the time involved both regional Police and
invited Experts from Scotland Yard in their solution.

Matt
