    'month' => '12',
    'index' => 'ef688',
    'body' => 'As I see it, Streetwise will help you find a bribable individual (though of
course it has many more uses than just that), and let you know the common
\'payment\' methods in this culture. Bribery is then used to assess *this
particular individual*, and know exactly how much to offer, in what form, to
both enhance the chance of success, and minimise the consequences of
failure.

Say, f\'rinstance, you need access to a certain location. You stroll up and
the Guard refuses entry. You could just try bribing the guard straight away,
using Bribery. Of course this Guard may be one of the previously mention
\'Gangbuster\' pure-as-driven-snow types... oop\'s.

The smart play (if urgency is not essential), would be to use Streetwise to
find out more about the Guards, which ones are most susceptible to \'looking
the other way\', when they are on shift etc.  Then bribing *that* Guard, with
perhaps a +1 or +2 DM on the bribery roll as you already know he\'s bribable
from the Streetwise.

YMMV

Matt
