Hmm... IMTU I use the following organization
System Navy: All ships in the System Navy Typically the one 4-Star. Large
system Navies might have a 5-star.
Fleet: 3 or more \'Rons Typically a VADM but may be an RADM.
Group: Occasional term for something bigger than a \'Ron and Smaller than a
Fleet. Typically a senior Commodore or a RADM
\'Ron: 12 Line Ships and their escorts, or 12 lines of smaller ships
Typically a Commodore\'s command
TaskForce: operational but not administrative unit comprise of 2-20 lines.
Typpically commanded by either a commodore from some staff unit or by the
senior Captain.
Line: For ships of the line (10KTd or more), one ship and it\'s assigned
escorts. For smaller ships in the 1-10KTd range, 2-4 ships. For Under 1KTd,
typically 5-12 ships. Typically commanded by a Captain.

SDB\'s typically are commanded by LCDR or CDR, the senior man in a line of
5-12 being a CDR and skipper of one of the boats. A Line of SDB\'s would
have a Captain. An SysDefRon, typically some 60-150 SDB\'s, is a Commodore\'s
command... maybe an RADM. Typically, however, IMTU you don\'t find
SysDefRons as other than admin units, and only a few worlds have the
capability for more than one... and said capability is often split with
Patrol Cutters.

In a very wealthy system (TLC+, Pop 9+), the system defense navy will have
a 4-star... and the several lines of SDB\'s are part of each of the DefRons.
Typical DefRon: 3 lines of SDB\'s, 3 of Patrol Cutters, 3 lines of CE\'s in
the 1-5KTd range, 2 lines of DD\'s, 1 line of a CL. So we have (1 CL + 2 DE)
+ 2(1DD + 2 CE)+ 3(3 CE) + 3 (5 PC) + 3(9 SDB) under a Commodore, maybe an
RADM.
Hmm... that\'s
1 CL
2 DD
13 CE
15 PC
27 SDB
as typical...

Why would you separate them out totally separate for a "Defense Fleet". By
keeping at least one mixed DefRon, you make the Ron non-deployable... and
as a system fleet, that helps prevent imperial activiation.

