Well, consider that the oceans, etc are a *very* thin skin on a planet.
The deepest trench is only 7 miles deep, and the tallest mountian is
around 5 miles. That gives 12 miles as a range.

The radius of the planet is about 4000 miles. 12/4000 = .003. That\'s a
*minscule* fraction of the radius. 

Thus the "easy" answer is that they were off a trifle in setting the
radius of effect. :-)

