    'topic' => ' Naval rank question',
    'body' => 'Swordworlder wrote:
> Bloody Coast Guard, that\'s what they are.  They deserve no Naval rank at
> all.  A JG could handle a silly PT boat like an SDB and a light commander
> would be wasted running the whole canoe club!  If you really must give the
> sorry sot a title then Bathtub Commodore should cover it.  Harrumph.

That\'s pretty close to how I run it -- a 400-ton tech-12 SDB is normally
commanded by a lieutenant; the jump shuttle, if present, is commanded by
a sublieutenant.  Most of the crew are ratings.  A 50-ship wing would be
led by a commander.  The planetary navy is led by an officer with a rank
no higher than commodore, as per High Guard; most planets have less than
one squadron-equivalent of ships.  The occasional rich high population
world may have multiple squadron-equivalents and several commodores, with
a senior commodore in charge.  The subsector (or "reserve" or "colonial")
fleet which is raised by the local duke is commanded by a fleet admiral;
it consists of squadrons on loan from planetary navies, and a cadre of
squadrons permanently under subsector command made up of surplus Imperial
ships.   

IMTU, the Imperium discourages planetary navies from having an admiral
rank -- it\'s considered a challenge to subsector authority.

  -- Steve Bonneville
