    'date' => 'Fri, 3 Dec 1999 11:07:33 EST',
    'body' => 'Actually, I did some work along these lines using the CHView program
for the First In Designer\'s Notes.  Unfortunately that article only appeared
on Pyramid, so if you\'re not a subscriber. . .

The gist was that:

1) I capped jump ranges at about 9 light-years, and assumed that this
represented Jump-2.  I used a linear relationship between jump number
and range, so that jump-1 was 4.5 light-years.  That kept the expected
number of destinations reasonable (i.e. greater than zero, but less than
ten or so).

2) You won\'t get "mains" of jump-1 accessible stars.  With the range
assumptions I made above, though, you\'ll get "chains" of jump-2
accessible stars reaching in several directions outward from Sol.

- ----
