No, I\'m thinking of a CT or MT source. I know that the tug in Supp 9 uses a
"Net" to haul cargo. The net is not essential except for jump. This
*IMPLIES* a grid of some kind, but is nowhere near explicit.

IMTU, there are several types of J-Drives, each with merits and flaws...
Standard Imperial (And everybody else by the time of the late 3I): Normal
book costs, performances, etc. Normal Drawbacks. Lanthanum Hull Grid,
Zucchai Crystals to initiate the jump proper, the J-Drive runs solely
during run-up, to pump near explosive-decompensation ammounts of energy
into the Z-crystals, which feed the grid. Note, I use MT...
Jn	0	1	2	3	4	5	6
Tjd	1%	2%	3%	4%	5%	6%	7%
Tjf	5%	10%	15%	20%	25%	30%	35%

Coil based: Major differences from SIJD are that the JDrive requires less
energy to initiate, but stays active throughout the jump. They take half
the energy (and thus half the time) to initiate a jump. (The coil
discharges the repellency field down to 1m fast... unless kept charged).
Also, J-Drive hits not only reduce max range, but increase misjump chance.
If drive damaged or fails or is turned off during jump, apply destroyed
mishap in 1d6x10 minutes unless jump exit occurs first.
Jn	0	1	2	3	4	5	6
Tjd	1%	2%	3%	4%	5%	6%	7%
Tjf	5%	10%	20%	30%	40%	50%	60%

Irridium based drives: as above types, max Jn reduced by one for same size
and fuel, misjump chance increased by +1, cost 75%.
So Irridium Grid drives
Jn	0	1	2	3	4	5	6
Tj	2%	3%	4%	5%	6%	7%	8%
Tfj	10%	15%	20%	25%	30%	35%	40%

Irridium Coil Drives
Jn	0	1	2	3	4	5	6
Tjd	2%	3%	4%	5%	6%	7%	8%
Tjf	10%	20%	30%	40%	50%	60%	70%

Stutterwarp
n+int((disp^0.666)/(TL-9))% of tonnage=nC, power draw is 250MW/ton (1HG
EP/ton). JDrive hits reduce n.
Min TL 10, Max Speed = (TL-9)^4. Only used in the islands cluster....
Limited only by PP fuel. Cost per ton same as Std J-drives. No misjump (but
also very slow).

Note also that I allow the J-0 drive; limited to about 1ly. it takes 5j0 to
reach alpha Centari... TL 9, although manufacturable at late TL8.

