work and whatever blind submissions they cared to send him, that would be
HIS upon reciept and that he wouldn\'t have to pay anything if/untill
publication. This with a track record of NEVER having published one thing
(new or purchased from DGP). Thier counter offer of a minimal payment on
reciept of solicited material and the balance due upon publication offended
him. Needless to say the deal fell through.

This was 1 or 2 years ago. To date Rodger (You know what goes here!) still
hasn\'t published anything. And has a number of outstanding debts to several
people for work done for DGP and solicited by himself anfter taking over
DGP.

Mike

