    'month' => '12',
    'index' => 'ef892',
    'body' => 'Don\'t despair...

Finding reliable, stable, free web space is an ongoing / recurring problem
for many.  Providers start out bending over backward to please customers,
but they are bought or otherwise come to a point of changing policy, after
which they insist on pop-ups or banners or some such full of advertising.
Or the owner loses interest in providing the free services and abandons the
project altogether.

There is hope...

Downport.com was begun because of these very problems.  We were not certain
in the beginning (last March) that we would be able to do it right
ourselves, but we determined to try.  We started out with a small, paid
account with a large provider.  We have since upgraded to an account with
more space and features with a smaller provider who have proved quite
reliable and responsive.  The next step in the process will be to migrate to
in-house servers so that we can have unlimited space and usage, set up our
own user accounts, and offer mail, IRC and MUD servers.

The cost...

The biggest expense in this endeavor is time.  None of us have unlimited
amounts, certainly, and a labor of love like this can be allocated only so
much of it.  The monetary costs are not outrageous.  Some of the expenses
are recovered by having The Traveller Trader donate 10% of gross sales.  The
overage and hardware expenses are coming out-of-pocket so far.  We may try
to recover some of it later in the form of a set up fee for new accounts.
We\'d prefer to find a different way, but we do not want to place any ugly,
invasive advertising banners on the site.

The benefits...

The Big Picture (tm) goal is to have, for lack of a better metaphor, a big
Traveller Mall.  Though not actually tied together or interdependent, a
group of cooperating web sites can pool talent, eliminate some duplication
of effort, and provide a marginally organized and rich resource of Traveller
material.  They can flourish in a stable environment, not wasting time and
effort changing URLs every seven and two-thirds months.  And, finally, the
combined popularity of the "Mall" may provide an environment where a
Traveller microbusiness could profitably run and cover the expenses of the
entire community.

So far...

To date we have brought Freelance Traveller, HIWG, The Traveller Trader,
AM-V\'s design house, the Traveller Webring admin pages, portions of Rob
Eaglestone\'s material and our own considerable content together under the
Downport.com banner.  It has already proved fruitful.  We are excited to see
what the future holds.

Count me as still dreaming,
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Colin Michael, WebDev
The Traveller Domain
www.downport.com

