>tech sophonts. Per MTJ4 (?), their may have been archeological material
>on Kirur itself to aid them, but that could be argued for any species.

I dug my copy of MTJ4 out to check. The timeline does not go into 
detail, but when the Droashav invaded the Kirur system, the K\'Kree 
could not have been above TL 7. After defeating the Droashav on 
Kirur, the K\'Kree then attacked the main base on Kirrixur using TL 9 
equipment. Yes, I know page 48 says K\'Kree scientists were 
miraculously able to advance 2 tech levels in a mere 25 years, but 
remember this is in the *player information area*, and the paragraph 
above that one says "K\'Kree records are hazy at this point". Also 
note that the K\'Kree did not invent jump drive at this time.

The referee-only section mentions the Droashav were at least TL 9, 
with one exception; they did not have jump drive. This section also 
states they had bases on Kirur itself, which were overrun by the 
technologically inferior but numerically superior K\'Kree. Later the 
K\'Kree reach TL 9 themselves, with one exception; no jump drive.

So the situation is one where TL 9 aliens invade a lower tech planet 
and begin slaughtering its inhabitants.  But the natives win. The 
natives reach TL 9 and turn the tables on the invaders. Now I agree 
the book does not spell it out for you, but which do you think is 
more plausible:

A: The natives ignore all the grav craft, fusion reactors, and laser 
weapons lying around the aliens have been using to subjugate them and 
begin a crash research program. Starting from nothing, the previously 
technologically conservative natives are able to invent all the 
invaders\' technology, but not other technology at the same tech level 
which the invaders did not have.

B: The natives reverse-engineer the captured equipment.

The important point, which the player information does not mention, 
is that the K\'Kree didn\'t have to travel to their moon first. The 
Droashav had bases on Kirur with grav and fusion tech.
- --
