to a 3D view, but that there are other layers above and below the
Imperium. With 10 layers, each would be roughly 10 parsecs thick
(which stretches the idea a bit) but means that out of the main plane
of the galactic ecliptic stars get more distant - each layer is about
half as full as the next one nearer the ecliptic. With less than
jump-3, only the main ecliptic plane is worth mapping since the others
are pretty much un-navigable.

