> (Vauxhall and Opel are the European parts of GM.)

There are other reasons to change a name, though.  Remember, the story makes
the assumption that Spanish speaking people cannot differentiate between
Nova, which is actually a word in the Spanish language, and "no va", which
is a phrase that looks and sounds as different as is possible for these two
syllables.

The tale also has an oft repeated second part, which is the "fact" that the
Nova\'s name was changed to the Caribe in Spanish speaking markets. This has
been reported in marketing trade journals. The truth is that the Caribe was
