"Near" binaries have the stars within a few AU of each other, for
example, as I recall from an old Asimov science essay, if the Sol
system was a binary similar to Alpha Centauri A&B, the second star
would be in the orbit of Uranus(?). It\'d be *very* bright in the night
sky, but wouldn\'t appreciably affect the seasons. 

