CT used jump coils to produce a spherical jump field  around  the
ship.  IIRC it was said (in the controversial A4: Leviathan) that
objects like antenea that weren\'t retracted  were  liable  to  be
sheared off.  In S9 the jump tug uses a net  wrapped  around  the
external cargo to extend the jump field beyond its normal sphere.
Evidently this  net  had  jump  field  repulsion  characteristics
similar to MT\'s jump grid idea.

Thus in CT a grid was only required in exceptional cases  as  the
non-grid field is a sphere.

(Additional: I remember reading somewhere that  the  CT  rational
for the 100d jump limit was that gravity distorted  this  sphere.
An extreme example would be a ship on the ground  activating  its
j-drive: the field created would be pulled into a splitter  shape
taking the j-drive, some hull plating, and part  of  the  landing
pad ... but leaving most of the ship behind!)



