I toyed with this idea for a while, and was going to write a 3D sector
viewer program (I have a very basic one for Dos which shows space near earth
out to about 10 light years, though the stellar Data I used is probably
incomplete). An Idea I had was to reduce the jump distances, and use
interstellar brown dwarfs for refuelling. Not all of these would be charted
given the difficulty in spotting them, giving ample locations for secret
deep space labs or pirate refuelling stations and the like. Incomplete maps
of an area would make invasion of an interstellar state by another a risky
business for the attacker, as the defending state would know the space much
better. Naval maps would be jealously guarded state secrets, and not
available to the civilian free trader. 

I keep meaning to go back and do the map program properly, complete with
sector / subsector generation, 3d viewer, and route calculator (given two
stars and a max jump of 2, what\'s the shortest route?). I doubt I ever will
find time though.

- -Brian

