    'body' => 'An evil genius in the grad student dorm council here shows a brace of
movies every Sunday night; last night\'s picks were South Park: The Movie
and Starship Troopers: The Movie.

The merits of the film per se have been discussed already here.  I
actually liked the film more the second time I saw it; maybe it\'s all the
lead in the drinking water around here.  But the interesting part was the
audience reaction to it.  The elite young minds of America and several
European countries, our world\'s future leaders, scientists, analysts,
financial whizzes, and military brass, thought it was a "really realistic"
(sic.) movie with a great plot, although they thought the acting was a bit
weak.  They were peevish with me for cheering on the bugs and consistently
referring to our heros as "the Nazi pigdogs".  They thought that the
future world order in the film was "really pretty reasonable" and "I\'d
sure go for that!" (direct quotes).

I take comfort only from the fact that Citizens of the TML, regardless of
political viewpoint, are unlikely to take any comfort from this.

Kenji
