    'month' => '12',
    'index' => 'eg043',
    'body' => 'Terry Mixon wrote:
> A quick question. I have gotten to the point of doing the minor
>trade routes for the entire Spinward Marches subsector, having 
>mapped out the major and feeder routes. GT: Far Trader says to 
>use J-2 routes unless a feeder or above would save a jump or more 
>or if it is along an x-boat route. Would a minor route then be 
>able to use a higher jump route created by the major and feeder
>process? I can\'t see why it wouldn\'t but that eventuality was 
>not mentioned. If the route is already in existance, my guess is 
>that a minor route could use it but I wanted to ask for opinions.

The short answer to your question is "yes, minor routes can \'piggyback\' on J-3+ routes if doing so reduces the number of jumps needed to reach their destination."

The language on designating routes is rather tortured, I admit.  Part of the problem is that "routes" is used to refer to the amount of trade between two worlds, the path that trade takes, and the total level of traffic between two adjacent worlds.  Inevitably, this leads to confusion.  If there\'s ever a FT 2e, revamping the vocabulary will be a top priority.

>I sent a message to Jim Maclean but he must be busy and I never 
>got an answer.

Sorry, I got busy and when I checked my email again my "Traveller" mailfolder had over 2000 messages in it.  I\'m still digging out.

Jim MacLean
Co-Author, GT: Far Trader 
