    'date' => 'Tue, 7 Dec 1999 10:57:10  0800',
    'body' => 'I definately disagree with Brandon\'s opinion. Here is mine, so that he can
disagree with it.

In the Traveller universe, nobles run everything. Because of this, I assume
that the ambitions of nobles will provide the motivation for lots of
interesting adventures. Giving a detailed background for these guys will
make the adventures more interesting and meaningful. Knowing the power
structure of the Imperial nobility, for example, will immediately bring to
mind lots of interesting plots. What is the relationship between these guys
and the megacorporations? What deep dark secrets are generally known only to
the nobility? How much political manuevering is there within the nobility?
How dirty does it get? Is there an accepted code governing what type of
actions are acceptable and which are not? Do these guys take an active role
in government? In particular, detailing the nobles in a known area, say the
Spinward Marches, would add more depth to the setting.

