    'date' => 'Tue, 7 Dec 1999 11:08:10  0800 (PST)',
    'body' => 'allensh writes:
> This may have been discussed before; I freely admit I
> haven\'t been reading the digests much lately.
> 
> I got a copy of GURPS Space 3rd edition and was
> extremely impressed both by the new Ship Combat system
> (which I like far better than the one in GT) and by
> their version of the Modular Ship Design system. I
> found the fact that Sensors and Power Plants had been
> broken out into their own categories to be such a
> miniscule addition of complexity that I barely noticed
> it. This modular system is excellent. I was wondering
> if the various GT gearheads out there could advise me
> on how to use THIS system to create ships for GT. I
> know Jump Drives are quite different, but the sidebar
> on the topic in GT gives relevant information. Perhaps
> some "Traveller modules" for the GURPS Space system
> could be done?

J-Drive module: 3T, 10 MW, 1 space, 3 MCr.  A ship requires (J+1) modules per 100 spaces.  In addition, the ship will require (J*.1) tons of hydrogen fuel per space to jump.

Cabins: multiply volume by 4.  Bridges should probably have their volume doubled.  Neither is increased in cost or weight.

Drives: use TL-11 reactionless at TL-10.  use TL-10 reactionless or super reactionless at TL-9.  Use TL-11 super reactionless at TL-11+.  Use TL 13 contragravity at TL 9+.  Note that \'vectored\' thrust systems are half again heavier and more expensive than the systems in Space 3/e.

PAWS: the smallest PAW is SHv at TL-8, EHv at TL-9, Hv at TL-10, Md at TL-11, Lt at TL-12.

Meson Weapons: use PAW stats, but they start as SHv at TL-10, and base TL (for damage purposes) is 10.

Meson screens: use force screen stats, but multiply weight by .04 and power consumption by .2.

Not much else to it, really.
