    'month' => '12',
    'topic' => 'GT:Nobles Want List (was  Question)',
    'body' => 'Loren, thank you for casting your net in the troll-infested
waters.  I hope you don\'t get sucked in!

Things I want to know about Nobles:

1.  Integration of Nobles into Imperial Worlds.  How do the
Nobles operate on worlds that have an implied or actual
non-noble government.  How are fiefs arranged.  Does the
Imperium require worlds to cede control over sections of a world
to set up a feif?  Does the Imperium create concessions (a Baron
rules the ground starport, and another Baron rules the lands for
100 klicks around the Scout Base, and a third noble hold the
patent to a gas giant refueling station).

2.  Inheritance Laws.  Clear up the distinction between Birth
Nobles and Honor Nobles.  Explain how Imperial law or custom
handles inheritance of titles and properties.  If a Duke has
three children, and the eldest is his title heir, what happens
to the others?  Are they now deemed to be at one lower noble
rank level?  Are they dispossessed?  How is property divided.
What sort of confirmation or right of refusal does the Emperor
exercise over the lower nobles.

3.  Nobles and the Local Law.  What power (if any) does a local
Imperial World have over a visiting noble?  Can a non-noble
court try a noble?

4.  Nobles and the Military.  The Domain Archdukes have ion the
past had influence and command over Imperial forces in their
Domain, but this power was lost during one of the post Civil War
reforms.  How much control does a planetary, subsector or sector
noble have over Imperial forces.  What about Household troops?
Any rules governing size and equipment for these guys?  Can the
Imperial military give commands to Household Troops?

5.  Noble Obligations.  Either real or traditional.  Are there
any?  Can a noble be impeached by a higher noble?  What are his
forms of redress?

6.  Knights.  How do they fit into all of the above statements?
Some sample Imperial Knightly Orders would be cool.

7.  Non-Imperial Nobles.  An Imperial member state happens to be
a Kingdom.  How the the King, the Dukes, the Barons and the
Knights of this world fit into the hierarchy of Imperial
Nobility?

Hope that was not too much - I am obviously a very curious
person.  I have my own answers to these questions in MY
Traveller Universe, but I would like to see the answers for an
Official Traveller Universe (or a semi-official GURPS Traveller
Universe!).

Steven Charlton

