Nobels can be an interesting campaign setting, and solve some issues.

1. A Scandel at court campaign, drawing insparation on the Roman Senate, The Sun
King Court (al la Three Musketeers), and British Parlement. Mainly usable IMHO
as a freeform (live action) session. It will also outline the possable factions
in the Court (Hawkes , Doves, Expansionists, Pro and Anti Solomani et al)

2. Nobles in the Imperium.

What are the roles of Nobles. Are they judges, adminstrators or parasites using
taxes to fund their extravigent lifestyles. What are the rights and privliges of
nobels, and what are their responsabilities. Are they required to spend some
portion of their time at Core, or do they use Proxies?

3. Nobles as PC\'s. The diference between (using British system) Life and
Hereditary Peers. What advantages are bestowed that are usefull in a campaign.
What disadvateages are inherant.

4. Who\'s Who. Notable Nobels from the Emporer , to Lord Pondscum the Tax
Collector. Nobels who the characters can inteact, or expexted to have knowledge
on.

5. Life at Core. A detailed look at the Capatol, it palaces, Naval and Scout
instalations.

Hope this helps you.

Darryl
