    'date' => 'Tue, 07 Dec 1999 23:00:56  0500',
    'body' => 'At 02:18 PM 12/7/99 -0500, you wrote:
>Date: Tue, 7 Dec 1999 12:16:42 -0600
>From: Loren Wiseman <lkw@io.com>
>Subject: Question
>
>The question has come up in house WRT GT Nobles: What does the fanbase want
>to see. How much should e devoted to life at the Imperial court? What
burning 
>questions (about nobles) need to be addressed? 

In addition to all the great comments so far (I especially liked Jon
Zeigler\'s list -- hear, hear!):

Top Suggestion: Combine GT: Nobles and GT: Diplomacy/Espionage into a
single, larger volume (144+ pages). Call it "GT: Intrigue" or some such:
all the high-touch (and sometimes high-tech) means of manipulating friends
and enemies alike to do your bidding, and obtaining the information it
takes to do so. Cf. Poul Anderson\'s Dominic Flandry books -- now *there\'s*
a Nobles campaign!

Other ideas:

(1) Gentlemen and Gentlewomen -- the near-nobility: business tychoons,
high-ranking officials that don\'t rate titles, military officers. How do
they rate in the Imperium? What is their relationship with the nobility?

(2) Noble Orders (cf. Supplement 11, p. 35) -- how many are there? what are
they? what function(s) do they serve (social, political, military,
subversive)? 

(3) Nobles\' and Gentlemen\'s Clubs (cf. _Flashing Blades_ by FGU, pp.
34-36)-- social organizations for the nobility and nearly-nobility. How
does one join? rise through the organization? what assets are available for
members?

(4) The Traveller\'s Aid Society -- the most famous and widespread
gentleman\'s club in the Imperium. Organization, history, assets, economics,
dirty secrets, you name it.

(5) Imperial Courts and the Imperial system of law (since I see this as
pretty much the purview of the nobility). Jurisdiction, jurisprudence on an
Imperial level, High Crimes and Misdemeanors, manorial rights, etc. Also
includes "internal" Diplomacy -- diplomatic relations with the member
worlds of the Imperium.

(6) Code Duello -- or why are all these nobles carrying silver inlaid
revolvers?

(7) Imperial Bureaucracy! the *real* power in the Imperium, and the natural
enemy and prey of Nobles. How is the Imperial government structured? what
are the various ministries, and how do they fight^h^h^h^h^h interact with
one another? All the weird ministries: Ministry of Justice, Ministry of
Colonization, the Imperial Monetary Board <fnord>. I see one of the primary
functions of Imperial nobles is to keep the  Bureaucracy in check, by
having the power to jump "channels" with impunity and take charge where
necessary.
 
