    'body' => 'Brandon wrote:
Despite opinions to the
> contrary, Star Fleet is 
> _obviously_ a military organization.
(which makes their policy of carrying families along
> assinine)

Not too asinine. After all, they have "seven year
missions," don\'t they?
This is currently a problem for recruiters in the
military: women\'s liberation. In the "good old days,"
men only were in the military, and their wives
wouldn\'t have careers other than as mothers, so they
just follwed their men around to postings to obscure
and unpleasant places. And despite stories of "Dear
John" letters, most women did wait faithfully back
home for their husbands and boyfriends until they
returned from the wars.
Women\'s Lib has changed this. Women have their own
careers, and so when it comes time for a soldier to be
re-posted, she says, "hey, this will screw up my
career," and all too often, either the marriage or the
military career will end.
