> 1. How do I calculate temperatures on the surface of such a world?  I
> tried the formulae in "Grand Survey" for tidally locked worlds (same as in
> WBH, I believe) but they give me a "cold pole" temp of only -60 degrees
> Celcius or so, if I\'m doing it right.  The formula says maximum cooling
