One important point that i haven\'t seen mention is that the forces in
WWII/Korea/Vietnam were largely made up of draftees or reservists.  An all
volunteer force, like the ones the Finns fielded against the Russians in
the Winter War, will have a much better rate of firing troops.  They want
to be there!

Since the Imperial Army is the cream of regular forces (yes, I realize that
scum is an equally appropriate metaphor), they won\'t have this problem as
much as historical forces.

Another factor is the realism of training.  The US Army\'s training methods
stress training the way you fight.  Systems like MILES and training grounds
like the NTC at Ft. Irwin have revolutionized the way soldiers learn their
tasks.

The Imperial Army and Marines have incredible resources (like the ability
to rent entire continents as live fire ranges) and the technology to insure
that training is as real as combat, less the deaths.


