providing more of their own resources toward the project, and because 
NASA liked some of its "sexy" technology (aerospike engines and so on).
The fact that DC-X was originally a BMDO project rather than a NASA 
project might not have helped it either.

X-33 was supposed to enter flight testing in March 1999, but that\'s been
pushed back to next summer.  Then they\'ll decide if that worked out, and
if approved, a full-scale "VentureStar" is supposed to fly in 2005.

  -- Steve Bonneville
