    'index' => 'eg302',
    'topic' => ' Question',
    'body' => 'It would be nice to have details of the noble ranks, how many of each there 
is and what responsiblities they have, what area the rule etc. But I don\'t 
think the book should dwell on that for too long.

Details of the Imperial court again would be good, but not too much.

Most of my traveller campaigns have been based around a small group of 
Travellers (the PC\'s), their ship and the adventures they have. Any 
supplements I buy should improve the game for the players within the frame 
work of this campaign. What I\'d like to buy is a book that expands and 
explains the role of a Noble within the "standard" traveller game.

A book that explains what benefits and penalties a Noble can expect during a 
game. Some work on explaining why a noble would want to go travelling would 
be useful some help in detailing the nobles family and responsiblity, and 
perhaps a system for generating the Nobles superior. A knight reports to a 
baron etc but who is the baron what are his motives. This superior could 
create a whole host of plot leads during the game as he used the PC\'s to 
help him achieve his aims.

In short the book should have an overview of the Noble system, if the book 
is to be Milieu specific then it should contain details of the current High 
Ranked Nobility, the bulk of the book should expand the game for a Noble PC, 
and perhaps at the back a Sample Yacht with deck plans, guided tour etc. and 
make it a true nobles plaything and not just a merchant ship with extra 
staterooms and a bigger jump drive, give it a dining room and a decent sized 
Galley not just a standard starship galley. It should be like the QE2 not 
the Isle of Wight ferry.

J.

