I forgot to mention insurance.  If the ship had some
kind of loss insurance, that insurance was triggered
when the ship was missing for some period of time
stated in the policy, and the insurance company paid
the beneficiary of the policy, typically the owner. 
Who is the owner is set forth in my previous post.  

So now the insurance company steps into the shoes of
the owner when the salvagers bring the ship back to
civilization.  

An insurance company could be a patron, if it\'s
cheaper to send a few PCs to look for a ship than to
pay the claim. 

