    'ts-index' => '1999-12-08.eg364',
    'body' => 'Howdy all,

Seems to me that the salvage value of a ship is balanced by
1) rendering a mandated service to a ship in distress
2) personal risk involved in the above

Space is big, and Traveller is an often nasty universe to play in.
If you find a derelict, that-which-caused-its-deriliction may well
still be on board.

If the ship has a lean on it, the lean holder takes the ship minus
a (large) percentage of the equity, which is the finder\'s fee.  If
the ship was owned by the deceased/missing, salvage rights apply
and the ship is theirs, including all on board which is not owned
by some other entity (freight springs to mind).

If the ship has a pathogen, parasite, or pirate on board, then
fun may commence.

- -Rob
