    'body' => 'Yes, the training was off for WWII and Korea. Yes,
it\'s been improved now. What\'s happened is that armies
have faced the fact that it\'s difficult to persuade
men to kill, and have learned to train them to do it.
I\'d agree that modern-day Rangers do have almost 100%
firers. But other armies, not so many will fire,
because of their different training. This is why 100
rangers were able to hold off 1000 Somalis in 1994:
less than 100 of those Somalis were actually aiming at
the Americans.

There is something innate in man to make him fight,
but there is also something innate in man to make him
reluctant to kill.

KA Schuant

