Actually, I can see another possibile solution, if electronics keeps
getting smaller/cheaper, and computing power keeps on climbing for a while.

Just "seed" the area with disposable, short-ranged encrypted relays.
Actually "relay" is a bad term. More like an IP router. 

So you are only transmitting to the nearest router, which sends
packets to other routers according top whatever looks like the best
route that millisecond. After a few hops it hits the bigger routers at
and behind your lines. 

Between spread spectrum and low power, you\'d be lucky to pick up the
transmitters the *soldiers* are using from even a klick away. 

If the routers are small and cheap enough, you just lob them in along
with the "softening up" artillery barrage. 

