    'month' => '12',
    'index' => 'eg523',
    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Keith said:
>I think that there are a lot of games on the shelves, simply because to
>sell a game, you need to hook someone and then pump out supplement after
>supplement to feed their addiction and pay your bills.  Just take a look at
>how huge the White Wolf, TSR, SJ Games, and Palladium Games sections of
>your game store is compared to say, Holistic Design or Dream Pod 9.  A lot
>of supplements of a few companies, a smattering of rare games, products of
>terminally ill/dead companies and obscure games tend to fill up the
>retailers shelves.

Y\'all may be interested to know this:

I suggested to my FLGS that "SJG may be the saviour of Traveller", since it is
the only company putting out Trav in any form with worldwide distribution.

They turned around and said, "Actually, Traveller may be the saviour of SJG",
since many SJG supplements sit on the shelves for a L-O-N-G time before being
bought, while the Trav stuff barely hits the shelves before it walks out the
door. They have sold out of all the G:T stock they have ever brought in within
the first 2-3 weeks (often sooner).

;-)

Comments, Keith?

Which supplements do your distributors say are most in demand?
