By current Aussie laws, it\'s the buyer that has to do the homework.  If the
dealer was caught with the stolen car, he would lose.  If it wasn\'t
discovered until Walt bought it, he has no recourse at all.  The Auto Clubs
around Australia have been "trying" to get this law changed for the last 10+
years, but apparently aren\'t trying whole heartedly.  My sister fell foul of
this law in the early/mid 80\'s... and currently, a police officer friend
(copper mate), a detective, nearly got caught, but he discovered the car was
stolen before he purchased it.

