Any guesses where the "big score" is going to be located?  No, I
wouldn\'t put it *inside* the territory of that foreign government
now would I?  <weg>

The McGuffin in my game for the first two years was "the ship."  Now
that they\'ve found it, there will have to be another McGuffin out
there to draw them on.  Frankly, I\'m not sure what that\'s going to
be, but there are plenty of "minor" plot threads that could develop
into something major. See, I\'m a big believer in setting up several
pushes and pulls, then letting the characters plot their own course,
and that includes NPC characters.  Let\'s see what have the
characters got to work with...

Why was Akus Moby murdered?  Did he have something, or know
something, that he couldn\'t be allowed to pass on, and if so where
is it now?  Does someone still want it...how much?

Why were the lawyers dragging their heels so much?  Were they in
league with the government, the Spacer\'s Guild, that loan shark
Pele \'Pickaxe\' Hiiki, someone else...or just incompetent?

What does the local intellegence agency want from them?  Is it in
their interest to play along, and could they *not* play along even
if they wanted not to?  How about these two new characters that have
joined them, are either of them agents? For whom?

Why was an unknown group trying to hijack the Mae Lee when they
arrived on the scene?  Why was a squadron of SDB\'s in just to right
spot to stop the hijacking?  Why did those hijackers *all* commit
suicide when the ship was boarded...or did they?

What happened to Colin David, the missing engineer?  His brother\'s
body was found, but not his.  And what\'s the deal with those
artifacts they found in David\'s duffle bag?  Do they have anything
to do with anything?

Wasn\'t it awfully unlucky that the ship\'s extremely hightech jump
sensor was reduced to a slagged wreak during the attack?  Is what
they found in forward engineering really the remains of that sensor
at all?  How will they know until they spend some time trying to
reconstruct it?

Do the PC\'s have the "Maltese Falcon" in their possession without
knowing it?  You know how many people want that black bird...

...and we haven\'t even scratched the surface of plots.  It\'ll be
interesting to see where the game goes from here.  <g>

Eris
