Sure, but coal has a *lot* of impurities (just ask anybody that\'s ever
used it for heat about all the slag you have to shovel out). And many
of those impurities contain harmless amounts of radioactive materials. 

But the emmision limits for nuclear plants are *so* strict that the
*natural* levels of radioactivity of things like coal (and especialy
the slag and "fly ash" produced by *burning* coal) is enough to set off
the alarms. 

We really are overly catious about some aspects of nuclear energy.

