    'body' => '>(My definition of "pretty f*****g cold": when it gets down to -40, as it
>usually does at least once during the winter up here. That\'s *really*
>f*****g cold!)

- -40 is just a bit chilly. When I was a lad in Saskatoon I just threw on
another lawyer of clothing and skied to school. No problem as long as you
dress and behave appropriately. Now -60 is cold.

Here in Hogtown people seem to feel that -10 is cold. Leaving aside the
whole question of Eastern decadence, a large part of the problem is that
people\'s clothing, buildings, and behaviour totally ignore the weather. No
heatlocks in the buildings, so there are lots of cold draughts. And no
perception on Bay Street that a dress suit and raincoat, or short skirt and
heels, aren\'t the most sensible clothing for subzero temperatures and icy
streets.

Which would be amusing if these weren\'t the same types who control our
economy. I feel so much better, knowing my future is partly in the hands of
someone without the sense to cover up when they get cold :-(


ObTrav: Take a noble from the Core and bring them to the Marches. Sit back
and laugh.
