    'body' => 'In mail you write:

>>It _wasn\'t_ handwavium [oh, the horror]!  It was Monohydrozine!
> Note that a monohydrogen engine (burns atomic hydrogen into molecular
> hydrogen, H+H=>H2) is actually the most efficient chemical rocket engine one
> can
> imagine (though we have no idea how to do this), so the words were almost
> right...

"Single H" would be nice stuff. Bare hydrogen atoms (H+)

Mono-hydrazine would be *scary*. Hydrazine is (structurally): NH2NH2

             H    H
             |    |
             N----N
             |    |
             H    H

Basicly a pair of amine (NH2-) radicals linked together. 

So *mono*-hydrazine would be a bare amine group (NH2-), that\'d be
energetic all right. And even harder to keep stable than monatomic
hydrogen.

